-- Hughes Refuses QPR Request to Resign, Standard Says: Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2012-11-21T10:56:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-21/hughes-refuses-qpr-request-to-resign-standard-says-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the web.  Hughes Standoff  Mark Hughes  has refused a request by team executives to
resign as Queens Park Rangers coach, the London  Evening Standard 
reported.  Hughes, 49, would get a 5 million-pound ($8 million) payoff
if he is fired by the last-placed Premier League club, according
to the Standard.  Homeward Bound?  West Ham is ready to offer  David Beckham  a return to the
Premier League after he leaves Los Angeles Galaxy, the  Daily
Mirror  reported.  Co-chairman  David Gold  said it would be a “fitting” end
to his career to play for the east London team, near where he
was brought up, according to the Mirror.  Downing Return  Middlesbrough may wait until January to sign former winger
Stewart Downing from Liverpool,  the Sun  reported.  Boro could take the 28-year-old on loan before the Football
League loan deadline tomorrow, the Sun added.  Redknapp Offer  Former Tottenham coach  Harry Redknapp  is considering a
“mega-bucks deal” to coach the Ukraine national team,  the Sun 
reported.  Redknapp, 65, would get a 6 million-pound salary before
bonuses, according to the Sun.  To contact the reporters on this story:
